## The OSI Model: 7 Layers of Networking

| Layer | Name             | Function | Real-world Example |
| :---  | :---             | :--------------------------------------------------- | :--- |
| **7** | **Application**  | Where the user interacts with the network.           | Browsers (HTTP), Email (SMTP)        |
| **6** | **Presentation** | Translates data (encryption, compression).           | JPEG, MP4, SSL/TLS                   |
| **5** | **Session**      | Manages the connection between two devices.          | APIs, Sockets, Login sessions.       |
| **4** | **Transport**    | How much data is sent and how fast.                  | **TCP** (reliable) or **UDP** (fast) |
| **3** | **Network**      | Finding the best path for data (Routing).            | **IP Addresses**, Routers.           |
| **2** | **Data Link**.   | Transferring data between nodes on the same network. | **MAC Addresses**, Switches          |
| **1** | **Physical**     | The actual hardware and electrical signals.          | Ethernet cables, Fiber, Wi-Fi radio. |

